<subSubSection pageNumber="887" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="887">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="887">Note:</emphasis>
The application of this name is uncertain. Morales (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="887">Ruizia</emphasis>
3: 179. 1986) designated 
<specimenReference collectionCode="S" specimenCode="247.5">
Herb. Linn. 247.5 (
<collectionCode>S</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
as 
<typeStatus>
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
</typeStatus>
. However, this sheet lacks any Linnaean annotations and, as such, is not original material for the name and not eligible for designation as 
<typeStatus>
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
</typeStatus>
. Morales identified this specimen as 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Cav." authorityName="Cav." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Thymbra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="887">Thymbra capitata</emphasis>
(L.) Cav.
</taxonomicName>
and therefore placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Thymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cephalotos">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="887">Thymus cephalotos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its synonymy. Spanish authors have in the past used 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Thymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cephalotos">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="887">Thymus cephalotos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the sense of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pau" authorityName="Pau" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Thymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moroderi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="887">T. moroderi</emphasis>
Pau
</taxonomicName>
ex 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martínez">Martinez</normalizedToken>
(probably based on the identity of the Barrelier and Boccone synonyms) but Portuguese authors have also used the Linnaean name in the sense of what has recently been called 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="887">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Thymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Thymus</taxonomicName>
lotocephalos
</emphasis>
G. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
&amp; Morales (1984).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
